wimmers who wish to be trained in American Red Cross Lifeguarding and for existing lifeguards who wish to update their certifications. LIFEGUARDING Participants who successfully complete the course will receive American Red Cross Lifeguarding /First Aid and CPR/AED for the Professional Rescuer certifications. Classes are two full days and one evening, and participants must attend every and all classes. The cost includes necessary books and supplies. **Minimum age is 15 years old** DATES REGISTER BY DAYS TIMES COST May 19 - May21 May 11  Friday Saturday Sunday   4:00pm - 10:00pm 8:30am - 7:30pm 8:30am - 7:30pm   Students: $100 Members: $100 Non-Members*: $240  *Non-members must be UNT Faculty, Staff or Retirees. Community may only register for the Lifeguarding Course and Lifeguarding and CPR Recertification Course. Classes may be combined or cancelled due to low enrollment. LIFEGUARDING AND CPR RECERTIFICATION This course is for currently certified lifeguards only. The class is to update CPR and Lifeguarding certifications. Participants have the sole responsibility to prepare for the class. Participants who successfully pass will receive American Red Cross Lifeguarding/First Aid and CPR/AED for the Professional Rescuer  and Lifeguard/First Aid certificates. **Minimum age is 15 years old** SESSION DATE REGISTER BY DAYS TIMES COST 1 May 27 May 22 Saturday 9:00am - 7:00pm  Students: $75 Members: $110 Non-members*: $130  * Non-members must be UNT Faculty, Staff or Retirees. Community may only register for the Lifeguarding Course and Lifeguarding and CPR Recertification Course. Classes may be combined or cancelled due to low enrollment.                             Visit Us  Pohl Recreation Center        1900 Chestnut Drive Denton, Texas 76203         Mail Us   1900 Chestnut Drive Denton, Texas 76203       Contact Us   940-565-2275 recsports@unt.edu Technical issues?                 Site last updated on May 05, 2017  Disclaimer| AA/EOE/ADA| Privacy| Electronic Accessibil